Quantifying Zebrafish Skin Patterns Using the Sweeping-plane Filtration Topological Data Analysis
========================================================================================================================
Codes are associated with the manuscript titled:
"Quantifying Topological Features and Irregularities in Zebrafish Patterns Using the Sweeping-plane Filtration"

Version 1.0
(C) 2025/09/30
Nour Khoudari, John T. Nardini, Alexandria Volkening

A sweeping-plane filtration TDA pipeline that:

1. Generates binary images from zebrafish skin pattern simulation data based on a (TDA informed) user defined pixel size. 
Simulations correspond to an agent-based model [A. Volkening and B. Sandstede, Iridophores as a source of robustness 
in zebrafish stripes and variability in Danio patterns, Nat. Commun., 9 (2018)] and can be found on Figshare: M. McGuirl, 
A. Volkening, and B. Sandstede, Zebrafish simulation data, 2020.

2. Computes persistence homology 

3. Classifies and quantifies binary images of patterns based on persistence barcodes.

