Files
========================================================================================================================

generate_binary_image.m      	      	generates binary image from simulation data based on a user defined pixel size.
										We use a pixel size stepX = 80 [\\mum] and two data set of 1000 simulation each, 
										the user can choose between two data sets
										dataset = 1 for wild-type zebrafish skin patterns
										dataset = 2 for pfeffer mutant zebrafish skin patterns

										Simulation data sets used here can be found on Figshare: M. McGuirl, A. Volkening, 
                       					and B. Sandstede, Zebrafish simulation data, 2020.

methodsNardini_periodic.py				methods of sweeping-plane filtrations in TDA, adapted from the codes associated 
										with the paper: J. T. Nardini, B. J. Stolz, K. B. Flores, H. A. Harrington, and 
										H. M. Byrne, Topological data analysis distinguishes parameter regimes in 
										the Anderson-Chaplain model of angiogenesis, PLOS Comput. Biol., 17 (2021)

wrapperZebrafishCA_periodic.py		 	computes persistence homology and uses methodsNardini_periodic.py


classification_and_quantification.m     main code that loads all persistence summaries to classify and quantify patterns
